  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.night_ritus_dagger_headline": "Weapon Passive:",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.night_ritus_dagger_passive": "This weapon restores stamina when you execute a target. This effect is more effective in moonlight.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.night_ritus_dagger_lore": "\nLike its counterpart, this weapon was forged from mithril, but under the influence of moonlight. It was therefore consecrated to Nox Obscura, the goddess of darkness. What became of this dagger afterwards, no one knows.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.blood_ritus_dagger_headline":"Weapon Passive:",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.blood_ritus_dagger_passive":"This weapon restores health to the wielder when they take another’s life.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.blood_ritus_dagger_lore":"\nThis was once a sacred weapon, forged from mithril, but it was misused for cruel rituals by high-ranking figures in the Blood Cult.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.vitreus":"The blade of this weapon is so transparent that you might think it were made of glass. There is a glowing, bright-red ruby on the hilt.",

  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.poleblade_text1": "\nThis weapon was used by the Blood Cult’s elite soldiers during the Unholy War. After that, it vanished without a trace and was never found…",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.poleblade_text2":"\nuntil now…",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.bonecutting_saw_text1":"\"Tantum qui viam mali ambulant ei digni erunt.\"",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.bonecutting_saw_text2":"\nThis weapon was primarily used by the Eques Mortis as an instrument of execution. After the Revolution, these weapons became a symbol of atrocity and were subsequently banned. Nevertheless, some of these examples are still in circulation today.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.iron_fist":"This weapon was used for torture by the dungeon guards of the old kingdom.\nThe pointed prongs make it look like a fist-sized version of the Iron Maiden.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.nailbat":"It is lightly smeared with blood...",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.saber": "Following reunification, a neutral party was established to uphold peace. To meet this challenge, they were entrusted with sacred sabres, whose ornamentation embodies the imagery of justice.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.milady_passive":"Press Z to switch Stances",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.milady_lore":"A light greatsword; that is, a sword whose blade matches the length of a greatsword, while being constrained to a minimal weight.\nNicknamed after ladies of noble status for its refined appearance. With cultivated form, one can wield this weapon as swiftly as one might a straight sword.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.poleblade_blade_part": "It appears to be part of an ancient weapon",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.nail": "That looks pretty sharp",
  "item.epicfight_dd.poleblade_blade_part":"Poleblade Blade Part",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.peridot": "Bright green, but no more dangerous than a pebble",
  "pack.16xTrails.title": "DawnDay 16x16 Trails",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.ruby": "This deep wine-red stone seems to absorb all light.",
  "tooltip.epicfight_dd.amber": "One might think this stone had captured the sun, as it looks as though it’s glowing a bright orange."
}